Agave fourcroydes

    Authority   Lemaire
      Family    Liliopsida:Liliidae:Asparagales:Agavaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names henequen, Yucatan sisal, henequem, jenequem, sisal branco
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2896

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A monocarpic rosette plant forming a 1-1.5 m tall
   trunk. The leaves are mostly 1-2 m long. Towards the end of its
   lifespand it produces a 5-7 m tall pole with yellow flowers. USES It is
   grown as a fiber crop. Fibers are used as binder and baler twine.
   KILLING T Damaged at -5Â°C. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. It require 4-6
   years to first harvest, and leaves can subsequently be harvested twice
   a year. In Mexico the plant has a life cycle of 15-30 years. COMMON
   NAMES Henequen, Yacci, White sisal. FURTHER INF Henequen is commenly
   grown in the Yucatan peninsula of Mexico and in Cuba. It thrives in dry
   tropical climates.

   Sources
   SOURCES (A. fourcroydes Lemaire)
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 11-14 [USE, DEP, DRA, RAIN, TEMP, LIG]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 121 [USE, DRA, TEMP, RAIN]
   Duke J 1975 pp 5 [RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Gentry H 1982 pp 652
   Kirby R 1963 pp 254-259 [TEXT, DRA, TEMP, RAIN, LIG]

